<item>
            <title>[PIG-4124] Command for Python streaming udf should be configurable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4124</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In my cluster, multiple versions of python are installed such as python2.6, python2.7, etc. Since some modules are only available on non-default python versions, it would be nice if the python command could be configurable by the user.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For eg, I have a streaming udf that imports pytz. It fails with the following error if it runs with &lt;tt&gt;python&lt;/tt&gt;-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
: Caused by: org.apache.pig.impl.streaming.StreamingUDFException: LINE 4: ImportError: No module named pytz
: File /mnt1/&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;var&lt;/span&gt;/lib/hadoop/nm-local-dir/usercache/cheolsoop/appcache/application_1407968511815_0021/container_1407968511815_0021_01_001322/tmp/udfs.py, line 4, in &amp;lt;module&amp;gt;
: &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; pytz
: at org.apache.pig.impl.builtin.StreamingUDF$ProcessErrorThread.run(StreamingUDF.java:519)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But it works if I use &lt;tt&gt;python2.7&lt;/tt&gt; as command.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
